The paper presents an algorithm for monitoring the connectivity of undirected networks in real-time, which involves analyzing the network structure represented by a graph in the datastream framework. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.IT (Information Theory). Among these, cs.DS is the most likely category as the paper focuses on developing an algorithm for characterizing the biconnectivity properties of undirected networks. The other categories are also relevant as the paper deals with real-time monitoring of network connectivity, which involves networking and information architecture, social and information networks, and systems and control. Information theory is also relevant as the paper discusses the space and time bounds of the algorithm.
